Poliovirus Weekly Update as of 16 Oct 2019, World Health Organization
----------------------------------
New wild poliovirus isolates reported this week:
AFP cases: 0
Environment: 2
Other: 0

New cVDPV isolates reported this week:
AFP cases: 0
Environment: 2
Others: 1

Headlines
- Preparations for World Polio Day taking place next week on [24 Oct 2019] are in full swing. On that day, the Global Commission for the Certification of Poliomyelitis Eradication (GCC) is expected to declare poliovirus type 3 (WPV3) as globally eradicated. The event will be broadcast on the internet. Viewers are welcome to follow the proceedings through a WebEx broadcast that will be available [at https://who-meeting.webex.com/webappng/sites/who-meeting/meeting/download/eb771ad22f8349eebc48c715ccee0fe9?siteurl=who-meeting&MTID=mc6de133ddfff591d99190733c4b8ef67].

- The Polio Oversight board met on [6 Sep 2019] for its 3rd meeting of the year [2019] to discuss the current status of work within the programme. The meeting summary is now available [at http://polioeradication.org/wp-content/uploads/2016/07/POB-meeting-summary-20190906.pdf].

Summary of new viruses (AFP cases and ES positives) this week:
- Pakistan - 2 WPV1-positive environmental samples;
- Philippines - 2 cVDPV1-positive environmental samples.

Afghanistan
- No cases of wild poliovirus type 1 (WPV1) were reported this week. There are 16 WPV1 cases reported in 2019. There were 21 WPV1 cases reported in 2018.

Pakistan
- No cases of wild poliovirus type 1 (WPV1) were reported this week. There are 72 WPV1 cases reported in 2019. In 2018, there were 12 WPV1 cases.
- 2 WPV1-positive environmental samples were reported: 1 each from Karachi Orangi and Karachi Landhi in Sindh province. The samples were collected on [24 and 25 Sep 2019].

Nigeria
- No case of circulating vaccine-derived poliovirus type 2 (cVDPV2) was reported this week. There are 16 cVDPV2 cases reported in 2019. There were 34 cVDPV2 cases in 2018.

Lake Chad
- No case of circulating vaccine-derived poliovirus type 2 (cVDPV2) was reported this week.
- In the Lake Chad region, cVDPV2 linked to the outbreak originating in Nigeria has been detected in Niger (1 case in 2019 and 10 cases in 2018 and in Cameroon (1 positive environmental sample, collected on [20 Apr 2019] in Extreme Nord).
- The risk of further cVDPV2 spread across the Lake Chad subregion remains high.

Benin
- No case of cVDPV2 was reported this week. There is one cVDPV2 case in 2019 linked to Jigawa outbreak in Nigeria.
- The risk of further cVDPV2 spread across West Africa remains high.

Ghana
- No case of cVDPV2 was reported this week. There are 2 cVDPV2 cases in 2019 linked to Jigawa outbreak in Nigeria.
- Surveillance is being strengthened in neighbouring Togo, Cote d'Ivoire and Burkina Faso.
- The risk of further cVDPV2 spread across West Africa remains high.

Democratic Republic of the Congo (DR Congo)
- No case of cVDPV2 was reported this week. There are 34 cVDPV2 cases in 2019 and 20 in 2018.

Angola
- No case of cVDPV2 was reported this week. There is a total of 18 cVDPV2 cases from 6 outbreaks reported in 2019.

Central African Republic:
- No case of cVDPV2 was reported this week. There are 10 reported cases in 2019 from 5 different outbreaks of cVDPV2 in 2019.

Horn of Africa
- No case of circulating vaccine-derived poliovirus type 2 (cVDPV2) was reported this week. There are 2 cVDPV2 cases reported in 2019.
Somalia has reported a total of 15 cVDPV cases (8 type 2, 6 type 3 and 1 coinfection of both type 2 and type 3) since the beginning of the outbreaks. The most recent cVDPV3 virus was from an AFP case from Runingod district, Middle Shabelle province with an onset date of paralysis on [7 Sep 2018]. Circulating VDPV2 has also been detected during 2018 in one environmental sample in Kenya collected on [21 Mar 2018]. There are also 2 reported cases of cVDPV2 in Ethiopia, linked to Somalia in 2019.

Papua New Guinea
- No new cases of circulating vaccine-derived poliovirus type 1 (cVDPV1) were reported this week. There were 26 cases reported in 2018.

Mozambique
- No case of circulating vaccine-derived poliovirus type 2 (cVDPV2) was been reported this week. There was one case reported in 2018.

Indonesia
- No circulating vaccine-derived poliovirus type 1 (cVDPV1) cases were reported this week. One cVDPV1 case was reported in 2018 from Papua province with onset of paralysis on [28 Nov 2018].
- This outbreak is not linked to the cVDPV1 in neighbouring Papua New Guinea.

Iran
- No new WPV1-positive environmental samples were reported this week. In total, 3 WPV1-positive environmental samples have been reported in 2019, all from Sistan and Balochistan province. The isolated viruses have been detected in environmental samples only, and genetic sequencing confirms that they are linked to WPV1 circulating in Karachi, Pakistan.

China
- No cVDPV2 cases were reported this week. The total number of cVDPV2 cases in the country remains one.

Myanmar
- No circulating vaccine-derived poliovirus type 1 (cVDPV1) cases were reported this week. There are 6 reported cases of cVDPV1 in 2019.

Philippines
- 2 positive cVDPV1 environmental samples were reported from Manila in the National Capital Region. They were collected on [23 Sep 2019].

