[While the weekly report seems promising, with no newly confirmed poliovirus (WPV or cVDPV) associated paralytic cases, the media report above demonstrates that circulation/transmission of the WPV has not as yet been interrupted in Pakistan.

And, while there are no new cases of cVDPV associated paralysis, the persistently positive environmental sampling in the Manila metro area in the Philippines is of concern as well.

As done in previous posts, to visualize all of this activity, I am putting links to HealthMap/ProMED-mail maps of countries with poliovirus activity during the past 12 months below. The size of the list remains impressive, now with 20 countries: 12 in Africa, 5 in Asia, and 3 in the Western Pacific.

